<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Your Two-Factor Authentication Backup Codes</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
</head>

<body style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; color: #333; margin: 0; padding: 0;">
  {{> header}}

  <div style="max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px;">
    <h2>Your Two-Factor Authentication Backup Codes</h2>

    <p>Hello {{name}},</p>

    <p>You've successfully set up two-factor authentication for your {{appName}} account. Please save these backup codes
      in a secure location. You can use these codes to access your account if you lose access to your authenticator app.
    </p>

    <div style="background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: 15px; margin: 20px 0; font-family: monospace; border-radius: 5px;">
      {{#each backupCodes}}
      <div style="padding: 8px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;">{{this}}</div>
      {{/each}}
    </div>

    <p><strong>Important:</strong> Each code can only be used once. Keep these codes confidential and store them
      securely.</p>

    <p>If you need to generate new backup codes, you can do so in your <a href="{{securitySettingsUrl}}"
        style="color: #0066cc;">security settings</a>.</p>

    <p>If you did not enable two-factor authentication on your account, please contact us immediately at <a
        href="mailto:{{supportEmail}}" style="color: #0066cc;">{{supportEmail}}</a>.</p>

    <p>Thanks,<br>The {{appName}} Team</p>
  </div>

  {{> footer}}

  <!-- Tracking pixel for email opens -->
  <img src="{{appUrl}}/api/email-tracker/{{emailId}}/open" alt="" width="1" height="1" style="display:none;">
</body>

</html>